## Critical Information for Families

**Most Important Takeaway:** The three programs form an income-based ladder.[2] If your elderly loved one's income is at or below 100% of the Federal Poverty Level (~$1,325/month for individuals in 2026), they qualify for **QMB**, which provides the most comprehensive coverage—essentially functioning as a Medigap policy that eliminates all Medicare cost-sharing.[1] If income is slightly higher (up to 120% FPL), they may qualify for **SLMB**, which covers only Part B premiums. If income is even higher (up to 135% FPL), they may qualify for **QI**, but this program's funding is limited and may not be available depending on when they apply.[1]

**Application Gap:** The search results do not contain specific phone numbers, online application portals, or detailed step-by-step application instructions. Families should contact the **Kentucky Cabinet for Health and Family Services, Department of Medicaid Services** directly to apply. The official website is available at the source listed above.

**Annual Recertification Required:** Income limits reset every April 1, so beneficiaries must requalify annually.[1]

